    <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

    <p>
      Hitting your protein target after 50 doesn't require a nutritionist, a meal prep service, or hours in the kitchen. It requires knowing which six foods deliver the most protein with the least effort — and keeping them stocked.
    </p>

    <p>
      Greek yogurt. Cottage cheese. Eggs. Canned tuna. Rotisserie chicken. Whey protein as backup. Build your meals around those and you have a reliable, sustainable foundation for hitting 120+ grams of protein every day without making it a second job.
    </p>

