      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What are the best high-protein foods for men over 50?</h3>
        <p>Greek yogurt (17–20g/cup), cottage cheese (25g/cup), eggs (6g each), canned tuna (25–30g/can), rotisserie chicken (35–40g/breast), and whey protein (25g/scoop). All require minimal or no cooking.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I get 30 grams of protein at breakfast without cooking?</h3>
        <p>One cup Greek yogurt plus two hard-boiled eggs (prepped ahead) = 30 grams in under two minutes. Alternatively, a whey protein shake with milk hits 30–35 grams with no prep at all.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the highest protein food per serving?</h3>
        <p>Rotisserie chicken breast (35–40g), cottage cheese (25g/cup), canned tuna (25–30g/can), and whey protein powder (25g/scoop) are the top performers by serving size with minimal preparation required.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is Greek yogurt good for protein after 50?</h3>
